  object
  (str sectionId) (str 42998)
  (str sectionNo) (str 17)
  (str orderNo) (int 17)
  (str title) (str `Application of the Code of Civil Procedure.`)
  (str content) (str )
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42998&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 42999)
  (str sectionNo) (str 18)
  (str orderNo) (int 18)
  (str title) (str `Trial of suits by Registrar.`)
  (str content) (str )
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=42999&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43000)
  (str sectionNo) (str 19)
  (str orderNo) (int 19)
  (str title) (str `Admission, return and rejection of plaints by Registrar.`)
  (str content) (str `(1) When the Judge of a
Court of Small Causes is absent, and an Additional Judge has not been appointed or, having been
appointed, is also absent, the Registrar may admit a plaint, or return or reject a plaint for any
reason for which the Judge might return or reject it.

(2) The Judge may, of his own motion or on the application of a party, return or reject a
plaint which has been admitted by the Registrar, or admit a plaint which has been returned or
rejected by him:

Provided that where a party applies for the return or rejection or the admission of a plaint
under this sub-section, and his application is not made at the first sitting of the Judge after the
day on which the Registrar admitted, or returned or rejected, the plaint, the Judge shall dismiss
the application unless the applicant satisfies him that there was sufficient caus e for not making
the application at that sitting.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43000&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43001)
  (str sectionNo) (str 20)
  (str orderNo) (int 20)
  (str title) (str `Passing of decrees by Registrar on confession.`)
  (str content) (str `(1) If, before the date appointed for
the hearing of a suit, the defendant or his agent duly authorised in that behalf appears before
the Registrar and admits the plaintiff's claim, the Registrar may, if the Judge is absent, and an
Additional Judge has not been appointed or, having been appointed, is also absent, pass
against the defendant, upon the admission, a decree which shall have the same effect as a
decree passed by the Judge.

(2) Where a decree has been passed by the Registrar under sub-section (1), the Judge may
grant an application for review of judgment, and re -hear the suit, on the same conditions,
on the same grounds and in the same manner as if the decree had been passed by himself.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43001&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43002)
  (str sectionNo) (str 21)
  (str orderNo) (int 21)
  (str title) (str `Execution of decrees by Registrar.`)
  (str content) (str `(1) If the Judge is absent, and an Additional
Judge has not been appointed or, having been appointed, is also absent, the Registrar may,
subject to any instructions which he may have received from the Judge or, with respect to decrees or orders made by an Additional Judge, from the Additional Judge, make any orders
in respect of applications for the execution of decrees and orders made by the Court of
which he is Registrar, or sent
to that Court for execution, which the Judge might make
under this Act.

(2) The Judge, in the case of any decree or order with respect to the execution of which the Registrar
has made an order under sub-section (1), or the Additional Judge, in the case of any such decree or order
which has been made by himself and with respect to which proceedings have not been taken by the Judge
under this sub-section, may, of his own motion, or on application made by a party within fifteen days
from the date of the order of the Registrar or of the execution of any process issued in pursuance of that
order, reverse or modify the order.

(3) The period of fifteen days mentioned in sub-section (2) shall be computed in accordance with the
provisions of the ^1Indian Limitation Act, 1877 (15 of 1877), as though the application of the party were an
application for review of judgment.`)
  (str footnotes) (str `1. See now the Indian Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963).`)
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43002&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43003)
  (str sectionNo) (str 22)
  (str orderNo) (int 22)
  (str title) (str `Adjournment of cases by chief ministerial officer.`)
  (str content) (str `When the Judge of a Court of
Small Causes is absent and an Additional Judge has not been appointed or, having been
appointed, is also absent, the Registrar or other chief ministerial officer of the Court may
exercise from time to time the power which the Court possesses of adjourning the hearing of
any suit or other proceeding, and fix a day for the further hearing thereof.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43003&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43004)
  (str sectionNo) (str 23)
  (str orderNo) (int 23)
  (str title) (str `Return of plaints in suits involving questions of title .`)
  (str content) (str `(1) Notwithstanding anything
in the foregoing portion of this Act, when the right of a plaintiff and the relief claimed by him
in a Court of Small Causes depend upon the proof or disproof of a title to immovable property
or other title which such a Court cannot finally determine, the Court may at any stage of the
proceedings return the plaint to be presented to a Court having jurisdiction to determine the
title.

(2) When a Court returns a plaint under sub-section (1), it shall comply with the
provisions of the second paragraph of ^1section 57 of the Code of Civil Procedure
(14 of 1882) and make such order with respect to costs as it deems just, and the Court
shall, for the purposes of the ^2Indian Limitation Act, 1877 (15 of 1877), be deemed to have
been unable to entertain the suit by reason of a cause of a nature like to that of defect of
jurisdiction.`)
  (str footnotes) (str `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908), Sch. I, Order VII, rule 10.

2. See now the Indian Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963).`)
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43004&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43005)
  (str sectionNo) (str 24)
  (str orderNo) (int 24)
  (str title) (str `Appeal from certain orders of Courts of Small Causes.`)
  (str content) (str `Where an order specified
in ^1[clause (ff) or clause (h) of sub-section (1) of section 104 of the Code of Civil Procedure,
1908 (5 of 1908),] is made by a Court of Small Causes, an appeal therefrom shall lie to the
District Court ^2]on any ground on which an appeal from such order would lie under that
section].`)
  (str footnotes) (str `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 1922, s. 5, for "section 588, clause ( 29), of the Code of Civil Procedure".

2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid.`)
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43005&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43006)
  (str sectionNo) (str 25)
  (str orderNo) (int 25)
  (str title) (str `Revision of decrees and orders of Courts of Small Causes.`)
  (str content) (str `The High Court, for the
purpose of satisfying itself that a decree or order made in any case decided by a Court of
Small Causes was according to law, may call for the case and pass such order with respect
thereto as it thinks fit.

STATE AMENDMENT

Uttar Pradesh

Amendment of Section 25 of Act IX of 1887.--In section 25 of principal Act, the
following proviso thereto shall be inserted, namely :--

"Provided that in relation to any case decided by a District Judge or Additional District
Judge exercising the jurisdiction of Judge of Small Causes, the power of revision under this
section shall vest in the High Court."

[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 37 of 1972, s. 3]`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43006&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43007)
  (str sectionNo) (str 26)
  (str orderNo) (int 26)
  (str title) (str [Repealed.].)
  (str content) (str `[Amendment of the Second Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure.] Rep. by the
Presidency Small Cause Courts Law Amendment Act, 1888 (10 of 1888), s. 4.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43007&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43008)
  (str sectionNo) (str 27)
  (str orderNo) (int 27)
  (str title) (str `Finali ty of decrees and orders.`)
  (str content) (str `Save as provided by this Act, a decree or order
made under the foregoing provisions of this Act by a Court of Small Causes shall be
final.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43008&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43009)
  (str sectionNo) (str 28)
  (str orderNo) (int 28)
  (str title) (str `Subordination of Courts of Small Causes.`)
  (str content) (str `(1) A Court of Small Causes shall be
subject to the administrative control of the District Court and to the superintendence of
the High Court, and shall--

(a) keep such registers, books and accounts as the High Court from time to time
prescribes, and

(b) comply with such requisitions as may be made by the District Court, the High
Court or the State Government for records, returns and statements in such form and
manner as the authority making the requisition directs.

(2) The relation of the District Court to a Court of Small Causes, with respect to
administrative control, shall be the same as that of the District Court to a Civil Court of the
lowest grade competent to try an original suit of the value of five thousand rupees in that
portion of the territories administered by the State Gove rnment in which the Court of Small
Causes is established.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43009&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43010)
  (str sectionNo) (str 29)
  (str orderNo) (int 29)
  (str title) (str Seal.)
  (str content) (str `A Court of Small Causes shall use a seal of such form and dimensions as are
prescribed by the State Government.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43010&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43011)
  (str sectionNo) (str 30)
  (str orderNo) (int 30)
  (str title) (str `Abolit ion of Courts of Small Causes.`)
  (str content) (str `The State Government may, by order in
writing, ^1abolish a Court of Small Causes.`)
  (str footnotes) (str `1. For instance of a notification abolishing a Court of Small Causes (Broach), see Bombay Govt. Gazette, 1907, Pt. 1. p. 339.`)
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43011&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43012)
  (str sectionNo) (str 31)
  (str orderNo) (int 31)
  (str title) (str `Saving of power to appoint Judge of Court of Small Causes to other office.`)
  (str content) (str `(1) Nothing in this Act shall be construed to prevent ^1[the appointment of] a
person who is a Judge or Additional Judge of a Court of Small Causes to be also a Judge
of any other ^2Civil Court or to be a Magistrate of any class or to hold any other public
office.

(2) When a Judge or Additional Judge is so appointed, the ministerial officers of his
Court shall, subject to any rules which the State Government may make in this behalf, be
deemed to be ministerial officers appointed to aid him in the disc harge of the duties of
the other office.`)
  (str footnotes) (str `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "
the L. G. from appointing".

2. For instances of notifications issued under this power, see U. P. R. & 0.`)
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43012&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43019)
  (str sectionNo) (str 32)
  (str orderNo) (int 32)
  (str title) (str `Application of Act to Courts invested with jurisdiction of Court of Small Causes.`)
  (str content) (str `(1) So much of Chapters III and IV as relates to--

(a) the nature of the suits cognizable by Courts of Small Causes,

(b) the exclusion of the jurisdiction of other Courts in those suits,

(c) the practice and procedure of Courts of Small Causes,

(d) appeal from certain orders of those Courts and revision of cases decided by
them, and

(e) the finality of their decrees and orders subject to such appeal and revision as are provided by
this Act,

applies to Courts invested by or under any enactment for .
the time being in force with the jurisdiction
of a Court of Small Causes so far as regards the exercise of that jurisdiction by those Courts.

(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) with respect to Courts invested with the jurisdiction of a Court of Small
Causes applies to suits instituted or proceedings commenced in those Courts before the date on which
they were invested with that jurisdiction.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43019&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43014)
  (str sectionNo) (str 33)
  (str orderNo) (int 33)
  (str title) (str `Application of Act and Code to Court so invested as to two Courts.`)
  (str content) (str `A Court invested
with the jurisdiction of a Court of Small Causes with respect to the exercise of that jurisdiction, and
the same Court with respect to the exercise of its jurisdiction in suits of a civil nature which are not
cognizable by a Court of Small Causes, shall, for the purposes of this Act and the 1Code of Civil
Procedure (14 of 1882), be deemed to be different Courts.`)
  (str footnotes) (str `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`)
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43014&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43015)
  (str sectionNo) (str 34)
  (str orderNo) (int 34)
  (str title) (str `Modification of Code as so applied.`)
  (str content) (str `Notwithstanding anything in the last two foregoing
sections,--

(a) when, in exercise of the jurisdiction of a Court of Small Causes, a Court invested with
that jurisdiction sends a decree for execution to itself as a Court having jurisdiction in suits
of a civil nature which are not cognizable by a Court of Small Causes, or

(b) when a Court, in the exercise of its jurisdiction in suits of a civil nature which are not
cognizable by a Court of Small Causes, sends a decree for execution to itself as a Court invested with
the jurisdiction of a Court of Small Causes,

the documents mentioned in ^1section 224 of the Code of Civil Procedure (14 of 1882) shall not
be sent with the decree unless in any case the Court, by order in writing, requires them to be
sent.`)
  (str footnotes) (str `1. See now Order XXI, rule 6, ibid.`)
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43015&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43016)
  (str sectionNo) (str 35)
  (str orderNo) (int 35)
  (str title) (str `Continuance of proceedings of abolished Courts.`)
  (str content) (str `(1) Where a Court of Small Causes, or
a Court invested with the Jurisdiction of a Court of Small Causes, has from any cause ceased to
have jurisdiction with respect to any case, any proceeding in relation to the case, whether before or
after decree, which, if the Court had not ceased to have jurisdiction, might have been had therein,
may be had in the Court which, if the suit out of which the proceeding has arisen were about to be
instituted, would have jurisdiction to try the suit.

(2) Nothing in this section applies to cases for which special provision is made in the 1Code of Civil
Procedure (14 of 1882) as extended to Courts of Small Causes or in any other enactment for the time
being in force.`)
  (str footnotes) (str `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`)
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43016&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43017)
  (str sectionNo) (str 36)
  (str orderNo) (int 36)
  (str title) (str [Repealed.].)
  (str content) (str `[Amendment of Indian Limitation Act.] Rep.by the Indian Limitation Act, 1908
(9 of 1908), s. 32 and the Third Schedule.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43017&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  object
  (str sectionId) (str 43018)
  (str sectionNo) (str 37)
  (str orderNo) (int 37)
  (str title) (str `Publication of certain orders.`)
  (str content) (str `All orders required by this Act to be made in writing by the
State Government shall be published in the Official Gazette.`)
  (str footnotes) (str )
  (str query) (str abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812&sectionId=43018&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00026_188709_1523273740812)
obj_root_law_translations:
  object
  (str hi) obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  object
  (str title) (str `प्रान्‍तीय लघुवाद न्‍यायालय अधिनियम,1887`)
